# Milestone 2 - Static Testing + Manual Testing

## 2.1 Static Testing (Review, Inspections & Code Quality Improvements)

### 2.1.1 Frontend Code Optimization

This review analyzed the frontend for redundant styles, unused scripts, and opportunities to improve load speed. It also ensured CSS and JavaScript were structured for maintainability and automation support.

### 2.1.2 Improved HTML Structure & Semantic Layout

The HTML structure was reviewed for proper semantics. Page sections, forms, and buttons were verified to use accessible markup and enhance screen-reader compatibility.

### 2.1.3 Code Cleanup & Component Standardization

Code cleanup included harmonizing element IDs, removing console debugging code, and standardizing form validation components. These changes reduce maintenance overhead and improve test stability.

### 2.1.4 Item Reporting & Search Flow Refactoring

Rather than payment-related items, this project uses lost/found reporting and search refinement. The flow was improved to make item submission and filtering more intuitive, with better field validation and state handling.

### 2.1.5 SEO Enhancements

SEO improvements included descriptive page titles, meta descriptions, and proper heading hierarchy. These changes also support a more polished user presentation.

---

## 2.2 Manual Testing Activities

### 2.2.1 Functional Manual Tests Performed

Functional manual tests covered: 

- Registration and validation behavior.  
- Login and JWT authentication flow.  
- Dashboard item visibility and ownership checks.  
- Lost item reporting and found item reporting.  
- Search with type filters and pagination.  
- Item detail view and contact owner workflow.  
- Update/delete restrictions for item owners.

### 2.2.2 Usability & UI/UX Testing

Usability testing validated that the application is easy to navigate and visually coherent. It included checks for responsive behavior on smaller screens and consistency of the main navigation menu.

### 2.2.3 Accessibility Testing (A11Y)

Accessibility validation included keyboard tab order, label associations, focus visibility, and basic contrast checks. A11Y issues were tracked and fixed where applicable.

---

## 2.3 Defects Identified & Fixed

| Defect | Description | Severity | Resolution |
|---|---|---|---|
| Invalid registration input | Email validation allowed malformed values | High | Added stricter client-side and server-side validation |
| Dashboard ownership issue | User could view items that did not belong to them | Critical | Enforced user filter on dashboard data |
| Search pagination error | Page 0 returned invalid results | Medium | Clamped page values and improved query handling |
| Contact owner self-message | User could contact themselves | Medium | Added owner check before sending contact requests |

